ROS driver: https://github.com/ai4ce/insta360_ros_driver?tab=readme-ov-file

# Operation
`ros2 launch insta360_ros_driver bringup.launch.xml equirectangular:=true`

# Modifications required:
Comment out rotations in `src/equirectangular.cpp` lines 279 & 280

Adjust crop size to reduce clipping change `config/equirectangular.yaml` line 5 to 1380

To test out different crop sizes, you can use the calibration commands in the github, but you also need to comment out the same rotation in the `scripts/equirectangular.py` by **ctrl + F** for 90.
```
# Run the camera driver
ros2 run insta360_ros_driver insta360_ros_driver
# Activate image decoding
ros2 run insta360_ros_driver decoder
# Run the equirectangular node in calibration mode
ros2 run insta360_ros_driver equirectangular.py --calibrate
```